# Project Restructuring Plan

## Goal
Restructure the current flat `src/` directory into a modular `app/etl/` architecture as requested. This involves creating a new directory structure, moving existing files, and creating new placeholder/boilerplate files where necessary to match the requested tree.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is a major structural change. All imports in existing files will need to be updated.
> I will be creating new files for `aws.py`, `config.py`, `logging_config.py`, `loader.py`, `transformer.py`, `extractor.py`, `etl_job.py`, etc., based on standard ETL patterns, as the current codebase seems to be in early stages.

## Proposed Changes

### Directory Structure
- Create `app/`
- Create `app/etl/` with subdirectories: `core`, `models`, `schemas`, `services`, `pipeline`, `utils`, `alembic`
- Create `airflow/dags/`

